    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Front Cover and Related Components -
        Installation - Gerotor Oil Pump Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="7">
        <title>Gerotor Oil Pump Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_S26509098.xml" xrefid="S26509098" appearance="hottext">oil pump drive
                    (spline)
                </hotlnk>
                onto the crankshaft, .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650643" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/h13012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump housing plate and seal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump housing seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump housing plate</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place oil pump housing seal into front cover recess. Align oil pump housing plate with
                dowels.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If reusing the original gerotor oil pump assembly, make sure the marks added during the
                removal process are properly oriented for installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650644" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8657.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Gerotor oil pump assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide oil pump inner rotor onto oil pump drive (spline). Install the washer seal with outer
                bevel oriented towards the front.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the oil pump outer rotor onto inner rotor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650646" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh07/h07026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the vibration damper key</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tap the vibration damper key into place on the crankshaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650646.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH07/H07029.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Applying Loctite&#174; hydraulic sealant to front oil seal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Loctite&#174; hydraulic sealant to the outside edge of the front oil seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650647" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5211.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Pressing in a new front oil seal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place oil pump housing into a press and install a new front oil seal using the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_144.xml" xrefid="t2650603" appearance="hottext">front seal and wear sleeve
                    installer</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650648" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8664.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump housing assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align oil pump housing dowels (2) with front cover holes.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650649" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/h13019.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump housing mounting bolt locations</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 60 (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowels (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 25 (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place four bolts (M8 x 25) into housing finger tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place two bolts (M8 x 60) into housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Torque all bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_S265APPB01.xml" xrefid="S265APPB01" appearance="hottext">standard torque
                    value</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
